    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 997.1-generation Carrera S is a definitive example of analog precision. Power is derived from a 3.8L naturally aspirated flat-six, coupled to a short-throw six-speed manual transaxle. The chassis is equipped with Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), featuring recalibrated Bilstein dampers that provide exceptional lateral stability and turn-in response. To ensure longevity, the IMS bearing has been proactively replaced with a ceramic retrofit, and the cylinder bores have been borescope-inspected with zero evidence of scoring. The braking system utilizes four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing no signs of thermal stress. This vehicle has been maintained to a concours standard, with a documented service history confirming zero deferred maintenance on the cooling system and VANOS actuators. An investment-grade specimen for the discerning purist.",
